# personal-context.txt.example
#
# Copy this file to personal-context.txt (gitignored) and fill in your details.
# This content is injected into the gemma4-mem0 system prompt at deploy time.
# It tells the LLM who you are so it extracts only relevant, durable memories.
#
# Run `python3 push-modelfile.py` after editing to update the Ollama model.

Your context:
- Homelab stack: <describe your nodes, always-on vs WOL, K8s setup>
- GitOps: <Flux/ArgoCD, secrets approach>
- Work: <your role, domain expertise, years of experience>
- Personal: <location, relevant background>
- Tools: <strong preferences, e.g. FreeCAD not OpenSCAD>
- Goals: <what you're working toward>

Example:
- Homelab: Proxmox + Talos K8s, RPi4 always-on worker, 8845HS always-on CP, i9+GPU and NUC as WOL burst
- GitOps: Flux CD, SOPS+Age secrets, public GitHub repo
- Work: Senior platform engineer, 10+ years networking/DevOps/cloud
- Personal: Currently in <country>, relocating to <country>
- Tools: FreeCAD only for 3D printing, OPNsense for networking
- Goals: <pilot license, consulting business, etc.>
